---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { CONTACT } from '../site.config';

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'WebPage',
  name: 'Terms of Use',
  url: 'https://prosperityfederalsolutions.com/terms/',
};
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Use | Prosperity Federal Solutions"
  description="Terms governing your use of the Prosperity Federal Solutions website."
  path="/terms"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container hero-inner">
      <p class="eyebrow eyebrow-gold">Legal</p>
      <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
      <p class="subhead">Effective Date: July 15, 2026</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container legal">
      <p>
        These Terms of Use ("Terms") govern your access to and use of
        prosperityfederalsolutions.com (the "Site"), operated by Prosperity Federal Solutions
        LLC. By accessing or using the Site, you agree to be bound by these Terms. If you do not
        agree, please do not use the Site.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Informational Purpose Only</h2>
      <p>
        The Site is provided for general informational purposes about Prosperity Federal
        Solutions LLC's procurement, supply, and fulfillment capabilities for government and
        institutional clients. Nothing on this Site constitutes an offer, bid, proposal, or
        binding commitment to supply any product or service, and nothing on the Site should be
        relied upon as a substitute for a formal solicitation response, contract, or written
        agreement.
      </p>

      <h2>2. No Guarantee of Contract Awards</h2>
      <p>
        Prosperity Federal Solutions LLC makes no representation, warranty, or guarantee — express
        or implied — that submitting an inquiry through this Site, engaging our services, or
        participating in any procurement process will result in a contract award, purchase order,
        or other business relationship. Government and institutional procurement decisions are
        made by the applicable purchasing agency or entity in accordance with its own
        solicitation, evaluation, and award procedures, which are outside our control.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Not Legal, Regulatory, or Compliance Advice</h2>
      <p>
        Content on this Site relating to procurement processes, government contracting, or
        regulatory requirements is general in nature and does not constitute legal, regulatory,
        or compliance advice. You should consult your own legal counsel or contracting officer
        regarding any specific procurement, bid, or regulatory question.
      </p>

      <h2>4. No Guarantee of Accuracy</h2>
      <p>
        Procurement requirements, pricing, availability, and regulations change frequently and
        vary by agency, program, and jurisdiction. While we strive to keep this Site accurate and
        current, we make no warranty, express or implied, that any information on the Site is
        complete, accurate, or up to date. Always confirm current requirements, pricing, and
        terms directly with Prosperity Federal Solutions LLC or the applicable contracting
        authority before relying on Site content.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Use of the Site</h2>
      <p>
        You agree to use the Site only for lawful purposes and in a manner consistent with these
        Terms. You may not: (a) copy, reproduce, or redistribute Site content for commercial
        purposes without our written permission; (b) attempt to interfere with the Site's normal
        operation; or (c) submit false or misleading information through any form on the Site.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p>
        All content on the Site, including text, graphics, and logos, is owned by or licensed to
        Prosperity Federal Solutions LLC and is protected by applicable intellectual property
        laws. You may view and share Site content for personal, non-commercial, informational use
        only.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Third-Party Links</h2>
      <p>
        The Site may link to third-party websites for your convenience. We do not control and
        are not responsible for the content or practices of third-party sites.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the fullest extent permitted by law, Prosperity Federal Solutions LLC shall not be
        liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising out of your
        use of, or inability to use, the Site or its content, including any business or
        procurement decisions made based on information found on the Site.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Communications Consent</h2>
      <p>
        By submitting a form on this Site, you consent to be contacted as described in our{' '}
        <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a>, including by phone, text (if you have opted in),
        and email, regarding your procurement inquiry and related services.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Changes to These Terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may revise these Terms from time to time. The "Effective Date" above reflects the
        most recent revision. Continued use of the Site after changes are posted constitutes
        acceptance of the revised Terms.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Governing Law</h2>
      <p>
        These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of North Carolina, without regard to
        its conflict of law principles.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these Terms may be directed to Prosperity Federal Solutions LLC at
        {CONTACT.email} or {CONTACT.phone}.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-dark) 0%, #2b1147 100%);
    color: #fff;
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }
  .hero h1 { color: #fff; }
  .subhead { color: #e2d4f0; }
  .legal { max-width: 800px; }
  .legal h2 { margin-top: 2rem; font-size: 1.3rem; }
  .legal p, .legal li { color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.7; }
  .legal ul { padding-left: 1.4rem; }
</style>
